MDplot.R                         - This script will automatically plot the data from task 1 in R. The commands to run this
                                   script in R are ;

                                   1. set path to the directory where you have run Hermes
                                      path <- path/to/Hermes
                                      setwd(path)
                                   2. load the script
                                      source("MDplot.R")
                                   3. run the script
                                      MDplot.R(path)

MDplot.py			  - This script will automatically plot the data from task 1 using python. Run the script and 
				    pass in the path/to/run/hermes when prompted. The python script gives an additional histogram
				    plot showing the distrbution of the motions.

plot.py                           - Development version of MDPlot.py
